translation.Name: Easter Note - Checkup #1
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: Recently we’ve been receiving notice of a tourist displaying rather strange symptoms, It’s most likely not the infection that is sweeping the rest of the world, but it’s worth capturing the tourist to make sure a potential outbreak is quelled before it can even begin.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_3: Contact has been made with the tourist near Rano Kau, they showed clear signs of being infected. We made sure to bring our outbreak suppression unit with us just in case things were worse than expected, how it was able to get away from us so easily is baffling. Unless it can turn invisible it must have either gone deeper into the caves than we previously thought, or it went straight into the ocean. One way or another it’s underwater.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_7: Reports have come in that the sea life around the island has begun to display less than tolerable symptoms, namely skin decay, increased puss production and large oozing pores. We might have found out where that tourist went after all...
